At noon on January 25, Mr. Qian cooked some vegetables, packed them in lunch boxes, and got into his car without his cell phone. It's the same road we've been taking for years, from Wuchang, across the bridge to Hankou.

The road is rarely pleasant, to the Yangtze River Bridge, the two sides have placed a red plastic pier, which filled with water.

"It looks like the road is really going to be closed! "

Mr. Qian's niece is a Wuhan Union Hospital cardiologist, the only child of the 1990s, her mother in the South, the child in Hankou alone, except for work is quarantined.

"It's not supposed to take this risk. My niece's neighborhood is her father's house, near Concord, and there are many doctors living there, " said Mr. Qian, 63, as his mind raced.

But the three photos on the APP inspired him to feel like a doctor cutting, making masks and protective clothing himself. He knew that his niece had been using self-financed masks to replace protective clothing with disposable scrubs when visiting new patients with coronary pneumonia.

Out-of-town relatives in the group said, let her leave, do not take risks, our family to train a doctor is not easy. Her parents were worried, but out of their reach.

Big Brother is the biggest.

How do you help a child? There is no professional protective equipment at home, Mr. Money can only do, "send her food. ".

"PROTECT YOURSELF! " Through the door, through the mask, he put the lunch box in the corridor, a distant look inside the flowers like jade children.

On the way home, Mr. Qian's brain began a fierce process: Throw Mask, keys, coat, shoes to alcohol disinfection, take a bath immediately. We're GONNA scrub the House with 84 more.

Because, at home in Wuchang, he had a 93-year-old father, Florida, to take care of!

At 12:00 that evening, Wuhan announced a ban on motor vehicles in the central city.

Up and down the bridge, in and out of Wuhan, the flickering traffic disappeared.

Nine million people in Wuhan, in addition to tens of thousands of confirmed patients, many more, trapped in their homes.

God asked

"This virus is too cunning. " Mr. Qian continues to sigh.

The thoroughfare of nine provinces in Wuhan, where Merchants Congregate, is the place where the distant mountains swallow the Yangtze River.

The invisible virus, those rotating, not closed RNA, meet the human pounced on, to destroy the potential of the vitality of our respiratory tract.

It treacherous and sinister, in China, the "Rooster" Dantian outbreak, to the radiation of the country, it is all the vantage point.

The outbreak of the time and just in the peak of China's Spring Festival travel, the national "Gankun great shift, " it also seized the days.

Heaven, earth and man three yuan, with the virus a resistance, only the "people" this element.

Wuhan people, is the virus to choose the most serious victims, but also by the history of the choice to fight against the virus pioneer.

The Spring Festival in 2020 is bound to be the darkest memory of Zhang Bing's life.

"What did you eat for New Year's Eve? How could I forget? "

Because that day, Dad was gone. Later, my mother, myself and my lover were all in the hospital or in the shelter.

He wants to show the universe that he's weak, that he wants to go into a time warp and start over. But fate didn't give him a chance.

There is no "If" in this world!

Zhang Bing wanted to take advantage of the winter vacation and Spring Festival with his parents, his wife to find an island to hide under the cold and Humid Wuhan. "If only" could leave Wuhan earlier.

On Jan. 13, his 78-year-old father developed a fever, as did one of his father's poker friends. "No one thought about it until they were hospitalized and reported to be suffering from new coronary pneumonia, " Zhang said, when I was still in the hospital room with my father.

On the morning of New Year's Eve, my father left me in the ICU. Zhang Bing can not see him one last time, "brain Mengdi" to go through the funeral home related procedures.

On the first day of the father's ashes "sent up the mountain. ". Also on that day, Zhang Bing received a phone call from the hospital. He was also diagnosed. On the same day, his wife and mother also had a CT scan, which showed ground-glass opacity in her lungs, "but there was no way to do a nucleic acid test, so we had to treat it as 'probable. ' ".

In retrospect, Zhang said, the first month of the epidemic was the darkest hour for many in Wuhan.

Wuhan has a poster, "98 flood we survived, 08 Snow Disaster We survived, this Wuhan we can also survive. ".

Families fall apart. You don't just get through it. Zhang Bing couldn't sleep night after night. Pain, fear of the emotions turbid waves, and his just a leaf boat, simply unable to control the direction.

At that time, days like years, eyes are always wet.

"At that time, the hospital gave him medicine and he was isolated at home. " Zhang Bing remembers that he and his family were like a time bomb in the eyes of his neighbors. He could feel the neighbors' defenses, "This also can be understood, I retreated the neighborhood group, basic do not go out, except go to the hospital check, prescribe medicine" .

Hospitals are full of "People Mountain People Sea" , emergency rooms are packed with patients, some of them sitting on shelves in a street square, waiting outside doors for tests, people also ignored the "1 meter" requirement crowded together, some people holding the bottle line, some people because of breathing difficulties directly fell to the ground.

"For a while, there was no hope at all, " Zhang asked himself in his diary. "I don't know when he will be admitted to the upper house and when he will be better. "

Self-improvement

The city was overwhelmed by the outbreak. Medical supplies for the hospitals in Xiehe and Tongji have not yet been available, and supplies and people's emotions have become tense in the communities.

Mr. Qian is trying to figure out how to adjust himself. He soon received a call from a neighbor, "can not wait, we organize, one is to buy, do not crowd in the supermarket line, the air is too bad; one is self-temperature. ". He's in the neighborhood. We take turns with the method of food, statistics body temperature.

"We have to be on our own before help arrives, " he said, unable to give the virus time.

"every day we get up, we are busy cooking, eating and disinfecting, and gradually we have no time to worry, " said Mr. Qian, who got up in the morning with the window wide open and returned with vegetables and alcohol to disinfect his clothes and shoes. And then diluted 84 sterile patches. Table and chair, Wash Basin, kitchen equipment, scrub many times a day, "keep working is exercise. ".

He is proud that his neighborhood is the only one around the undiagnosed and suspected cases, "fortunately, each of our families are the kind of high self-discipline, rigorous people. ".

"Fengcheng" before, Meng Yuan (not his real name) heard the gossip, immediately went to the vegetable market. She felt herself in a state of flux, as if she were buying groceries, as if her front aunt had piled up not only a small cart full of groceries, but two large plastic bags.

Meng Yuan returned home, the last two cabbages stand, there are more than 10 catties of potatoes, turnips and other easy-to-store vegetables, the same at home.

Mom and dad came back from work, also scolded her: "Buy so many dishes? We go home on the first day. " Two days later, Wuhan really closed the city, many people rushed to the supermarket to buy. Meng Yuan, on the other hand, held on to the reserves for two weeks.

Meng Yuan's family began to separate meals, cooked meals with public tableware to Sheng, and then took to a different room to eat. Boiled water washed dishes were put in 3 different places, some put the kitchen, some put the living room. New Year's Eve dinner, three people sat together, but a meal down almost the whole silence, "no one dare to speak, for fear of spreading foam. ".

But the family's vegetables are still in a hurry. Meng Yuan, a phd student, studied various online shopping and shopping APPS, and came up with a shopping guide to count the time and place the order. When the take-out arrived, make an appointment to pick up the dish, wait for the delivery boy to leave, then go over to pick up, "just like the signal joint. ".

At a time when supermarkets across the city are bursting with shoppers, residents of Hanyang's Fanghui Garden community are in for a treat. Because there's a good man in this neighborhood.

Zhao Meng, 30, runs the rookie station. At the beginning of the epidemic, Zhao Meng bought 1 ton of rice, 1.5 tons of flour, 1000 catties of oil and 800 catties of noodles and put them in the post station. In fact, Zhao has been away from the station since the Spring Festival. On December twenty-nine, he joined the ranks of volunteers, driving to and from Xiantao and other places, for the hospital in Wuhan delivery of medical supplies.

Not In the Post Station, Zhao opened the post station door, a clockwork wechat circle of friends, let the residents themselves order to get supplies, and then through the Qr code payment. "How much to pay, the inhabitant oneself looked up the price on the net to take the average value to go" .

"For some time now, everyone has been paying consciously, and the materials in the station are exactly the same, " Zhao said, referring to the high quality and good character of the residents of the 1,400-strong residential community.

Zhao Meng is in fact a tenant of this small area, but he gave the neighbors who worry every day the greatest comfort, let "righteous memory" , naturally, "evil can not do.

On January 27, it was bitterly cold in the unheated room.

One person on Mr. Hu's Wechat,@all, from Wuhan, said: "People in Wuhan who are isolated at home are organizing a big event tonight, and there are people who would like to participate. ". Tonight starts at 8:00 pm, then everybody opens the balcony window to sing, does not sing does not disperse! After the chorus of "March of the Volunteers" , three shouts of 'go Wuhan' ! "

He immediately opened the window, there is a half an hour, "we have suppressed for so long, it is important to vent some emotions. ".

After less than 10 minutes of excitement, a self-proclaimed Concordia aspiration physician on the Internet hovered in the Hoo: "please stop the singing incident in the residential area immediately. It is extremely dangerous and may spread pneumonia! " Mr. Hu put on a mask and looked out, found a lot of home windows are open, face inconspicuous, "the building distance of dozens of meters, no problem? "

The doctor's words may have played a role, Mr. Hu community singing few people, but heard a lot of people shouting in Wuhan dialect, "Wuhan refueling. ". He took his son a meter away from the window also followed a shout, feel a lot more comfortable in the heart.

"It's not self-indulgence, it's psychological self-help! " Mr. Hu said, referring to Mr. Zhang Fei as "a shout from the bridge of Dangyang that ends the water flowing back from the bridge. " It was a boost to my prestige.

Wuhan is an important military industrial town, famous schools gathered, many of the pillars of the country living here. They carried it with the people of Wuhan. How could the city fall?

On February 12, post-80s Li Jing was admitted to the dunkou shelter hospital after being diagnosed with new pneumonia. Those days, Wuhan weather is overcast and cold, still float snow, Li Jing is incommensurate, wash a head to bathe go to the toilet inconvenient. Flustered, "worried about their daughter and parents by their own infection. ".

Until the fifth day, "calculate the day, the family should be fine. " Li Jing hung up the mental calculation to the ground.

She found out where she could wash her hair. After washing my hair, I went to the square of the Shelter Hospital. The Sun came out. She began to observe around the medical staff for everyone: wrapped in thick protective clothing, some very ordinary movements are also "stupid, naive" , like "Baymax. Part-time illustrator. Li Jing, who lives next to Yellow Crane Tower, has the stubbornness of the Wuhan People. There was no lack of ordinary everyday life in the shelter, but there was the power of life in it. Think of those moments, the pen tip with the thoughts on the paper, those irritable, boring, restless emotions seem to have been tamed, quiet down, sometimes drawing yourself even unconsciously laugh. Some people say that happiness, anger, sorrow and fear, after several cycles of transmission, the brave people of Wuhan built up psychological immunity to the virus. In the vast space of the shelter, in the rhythm of the music, the door of the unit is opened, and the psychological core of a group is "not convinced by Zhou" .

The shadow of his father's death did not leave Zhang Bing, he went to the shelter for two nights.

But he unconsciously enters a state of being like a man who spends his days in bed with his wife, like a man who enters a shared society in advance, sharing food and drink as soon as he sees them.

People will even do some nonsense, "for example, sometimes you fall asleep suddenly someone will take a snack hit you, very childish, like back to the childhood. ".

Usually feel tacky like square dance, usually feel childish like eating snacks together, in this collective war "epidemic" time, have become a healing agent of the mind.

"Let's call it happiness out of misery. Living in a group can enrich our time, distract us from anxiety, maintain a good mood and improve our immunity. Isn't it true that the most important thing to overcome the virus is our own immunity? " Zhang Bing said, "can we meet in the shelter? " I mean, we were friends for life.

On the day of his departure, Zhang Bing was transferred to an isolation observation point, which he called "the shelter PLUS  " , because the food was better than the shelter, and he was able to eat hot dry noodles and drink "Lotus rhizome spareribs soup" . Every day, he updates his circle of friends on the daily routine of "box PLUS. ". In his spare time, Zhang Bing washes all the laundry he can. When he is free, he also likes to Sing Karaoke by himself, and record some small videos to share with his friends. They have arranged to wait for the "Python" . Friends of life and death will go to a small restaurant for a get-together, with the wine and the conversation as usual.

Street fighting

"Don't think that the Soviet-german war was all positional warfare and tank warfare, but the most dangerous and Necessary Roughness turning point was street warfare! " Yū Hayashi (not his real name) was doing ideological work for eight party members who had sunk into the same street, "It's up to us to stop the infection, " he said, using the movie "Battle of Stalingrad. "

Yū Hayashi, vice president of a cultural unit under a Wuhan City owned enterprise, was ordered to sink into the street after the New Year.

At first, it was a relief to be at home. All Nine wore disposable raincoats, masks over their glasses and disposable surgical masks inside. Armed to the teeth, they pose in the Sun.

But by the end of the first day, he was gone. Hoarse throat, waist pain, lying on the bed do not want to move. At that time, the residents simply could not bear to be shut down and wanted to leave the yard. He kept explaining the meaning of the gated community, going from house to house to ask about his temperature, and finding out about the family of a confirmed patient.

It's a total job, Yū Hayashi. He's used to sitting in an office.

When it snowed and the street cadres collapsed, the nine of them became the main force.

Every day, he would call to check his temperature, do the charts, count the confirmed, suspected, cured patients, organize the shipments, leave at 7:00 a.m. and come home at 7:00 p.m. At the time, confirmed patients were quarantined at home, and he was in charge of delivering drugs and supplies. Worried about infecting his mother, he quarantined himself in a house 15 minutes away every day.

The "STREET WAR" , which began with lofty rhetoric, has now become "trivial" .

Once, a resident called a street hotline to buy medicine. He bought it and sent it upstairs without a word. Three days later, the guy says it's not working and he has to return it. His face was red with shame, but he had a mask over his face and told the clerk to return it. The clerk said, at that time buy medicine still have Freebie, that return together. Because the residents wouldn't give out the gifts, the shop assistants wouldn't return them. Commander Lin was scolded a lot of bad words.

Lin's liver ached with courage. The students from other places advised him that you used to be able to deal only with intellectuals, now you have to learn to deal with the grass-roots people.

At 3:37 on Feb. 8, Liu Jiajia of Wuhan City Flood Control Survey and Design Institute Co. , Ltd. Woke up in the middle of the night to check her mobile phone and found a notice on her work unit's Wechat group calling on party members and cadres to sink into the community.

Liu Jiajia thought about it and signed up.

He was dispatched to the Middle North road middle school teachers'dormitory in Wuzhong Community. This is a no security, no property "unattended" area, the need for someone to cooperate with management, on duty 24 hours.

In the makeshift tent, there were two stools at first, and the next day, lights and bunks. Liu quickly found out the residential community: 12 residents in a total of 24 people, including 70-year-old seven people, living alone in three elderly, there is a pregnant woman.

In the community, each volunteer is a brick that needs to be moved from place to place.

GRANDPA Hu, 70, lives alone and is running out of diabetes medication. Liu Jia ran to three nearby pharmacies and couldn't find any. It took him 30 minutes to buy the bike and deliver it to the old man.

February 23, in the care of vegetables, Liu Jiajia learned that pregnant women Li scheduled to March 4 to the hospital for an examination. On March 3, Liu Jiajia made an appointment for a caring taxi driver in the community.

On the 4th, Liu Jiajia was supposed to work the night shift, but thinking about Ms. Li, he came at 8:20 in the morning and asked Ms. Li to go downstairs and take her to a taxi. He also gave her the self-contained Aerosol of disinfectant he had brought with him. If you don't do it, do it right. Liu Jia Jia and told the security guard, Ms. Li from the hospital back into the community door to do good to kill, he thought, and back said, "kill process you want to take pictures for me to stay on file. ".

Due to his dedication, Liu Jiajia was elected as Wuzhong Community Provincial Epidemic Control Party member volunteer commandos and community leaders.

So far, no one in his neighborhood has been infected.

Today, Yū Hayashi has been working the streets for a month and three days. He found himself sleeping late and waking up late, and every morning on the way to work in a good mood, after lunch can sit in a chair for 40 minutes, adapted! "What is not always, disaster came, try to help more people to survive together. ".

Yū Hayashi had the strength to address the Wechat Group: Everyone is adjusting to what a state of war is, and wartime and past peacetime are two different things. When a doctor in a hospital falls, medical personnel from all over the country will replace him. When a street cadre falls, we will replace him. Just as the army is crippled, it will regroup and launch a new charge. This is the people's war of the general campaign.

Mr. Hu looked down from the 17th floor at the busy volunteers coming and going, exclamation: This Wuhan Communist performance let me admire! They're all wrapped up like doctors with no names on their backs, and they do all these little jobs, and we don't know who they are, but it feels safe to look at them.

"there are 100,000 who are trying to survive, 100,000 who are working hard to help us survive, and more than 8 million who are not moving, " Mr. Hu said. "It's also a kind of battle. ".

"I want the people of Wuhan to know that the world knows your contribution, that we are sharing your story with the world, and that what you are doing is very important. "

In this world-shaking pandemic, Wuhan fought against the most cruel virus and exported its value to the world as if it were unequalled tenacious.

Thank you, 9 million Wuhan people, Spring has come, the flowers are blooming, the sun is shining, you give China to the world to win time!

Produced by China Youth Daily
